The course will provide a survey of the major developments in 20th century British literature from Modernist poetry and prose to today's multicultural and multiethnic writing. The main emphasis will be on reading and discussing texts by a range of representative authors, including Virginia Woolf, W.H. Auden, William Golding and Zadie Smith among others. The course will end in an oral examination.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to give a survey of 20th century British literature starting from the Modernist movement to the turn of the millennium. The course will provide insights into the period's literary history and enhance the student's skills of critical discussion, reflection and comparison as of modern poetry and fiction.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course the students will 1) have obtained a survey of the British literary history in the 20th century 2) have acquired a toolkit of critical terms relevant to the period 3) have improved their skills of close reading of fiction and poetry
